 Port Elizabeth - Investigations are underway after three people died when a bakkie drove off the N2 bridge and plunged into the Swartkops River mouth in Bluewater Bay, Port Elizabeth, on Monday. Two other occupants from the same bakkie were rushed to hospital with injuries. Fatal accident N2 Bluewater Bay - Two vehicles - one has landed in the water. @ER24EMS @UnitedTowingSA @stanfromibf @JanineCLee @ettiennepel @IrenePretorius5 @EMER_G_MED @GardmedPE @AccidentAwareSA @EMERGCONTROL @_ArriveAlive @AlgoaFMNews @AlgoaFM @HeraldPE @RNEWSZA @MyPE pic.twitter.com/77E2etwId7 The accident held up traffic on the busy N2 Highway as Emergency Services and members of the public joined hands in saving people from the water. Image: PE Traffic Updates According to police information, the bakkie - a silver Toyota double cab bakkie, and a maroon Chrysler Neon, apparently collided on the bridge. Both vehicles were travelling towards the Nelson Mandela Bay at about 11:45 on Monday morning when the accident took place. It is also suspected that strong winds experienced on Monday might have played a part in the accident. Meanwhile, a case of culpable homicide is under investigation by Port Elizabeth police. Police will release the names of those killed in the accident when their next of kin have been notified. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 